It grants least‑privilege permissions to start and stop EC2 instances only:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "EC2StartStopAccess",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:StartInstances",
        "ec2:StopInstances",
        "ec2:DescribeInstances"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:ec2:us-east-1:729386419948:instance/*"
    }
  ]
}

ersion: "2012-10-17" is the current IAM policy language version.

Actions:

StartInstances → allows starting EC2 instances.

StopInstances → allows stopping EC2 instances.

DescribeInstances → lets the user list and view instance details (often needed to identify which instance to manage).

Resource: Scoped to all EC2 instances in a specific AWS account (729386419948) and region (us-east-1).
